On the twelfth of November Clodius attempted to take possession of and burn Milo's house in the Germalus, and Milo was compelled to bring an action against him for disturbance of the peace under the lex Plautia de vi. Clodius made vigorous efforts to obtain the aedileship‚ in the hope of eluding by this means the process with which he was threatened.
